10.11	Battle_of_Stony_Point	Battle of Stony Point	The Battle of Stony Point was a battle of the American Revolutionary War fought on the night of July 15â€“16, 1779. A select force of Continental Army infantry made a coordinated surprise night attack and stormed a fortified position of the British Army on the Hudson River south of West Point, New York. The position was taken in 25 minutes with the loss to the British of nearly an entire regiment of infantry.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a7/Battle_of_Stony_Point.jpg
